# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration Report

## Summary
Successfully updated and verified Vercel Web Analytics configuration for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation.

## What Was Done

### 1. Project Analysis
- Confirmed this is a Next.js 16.1.6 project using the App Router
- Identified that `@vercel/analytics` was already installed (v1.6.1)
- Verified that Analytics component was already properly configured in the root layout

### 2. Fetched Latest Documentation
- Retrieved the latest installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Verified the framework-specific setup for Next.js App Router
- Confirmed the correct import statement and component usage

### 3. Package Update
- Updated `@vercel/analytics` from v1.6.1 to v2.0.1 (latest version)
- The upgrade is backward compatible - no code changes required
- Main improvements in v2: MIT license, Resilient Intake feature for better reliability

### 4. Verified Configuration
The Analytics implementation follows the latest best practices:
- **Import**: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- **Location**: Added in `src/app/layout.tsx` (root layout)
- **Placement**: `<Analytics />` component placed in the `<body>` element after children

