## Files Already Configured (No Changes Needed)
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Analytics component already properly integrated

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component in `src/app/layout.tsx`:
```typescript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This implementation matches the official Vercel documentation exactly and will:
- Automatically track page views in production
- Collect performance metrics
- Work seamlessly with Next.js App Router
- Use Vercel's Resilient Intake for reliable data collection (v2 feature)

## Next Steps
To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Analytics in the Vercel project dashboard
3. Analytics data will start appearing within 24 hours of deployment

## Notes
- The project uses npm as the package manager
- Pre-existing linter warnings/errors are unrelated to Analytics configuration
- Analytics will only track data when deployed to Vercel (not in local development)
